
            Video
            The 'sound baths' rinsing off the day with noise
            The sound of a gong might seem like the last thing to help you drift off to sleep.But users of a wellness technique are reporting that lying down amid sound - or sound bathing - not only soothes and helps them switch off during their sessions in Stirchley, Birmingham, but helps their quality of sleep once home and in their own beds. "Sound baths" are a modern spin on an ancient relaxation practice tapping into "good vibrations".Video Journalist: Louise Brierley
                
                        13 Nov 2018
                    
                
        
